xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:7;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Security\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"https://community.1and1.com/?p=10122\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:623:\"<p>WordPress 4.9.7 is now available for download for all earlier WordPress versions. It also includes bugfixes and security improvements. Learn more How to update? As always, Managed WordPress websites will be updated by 1&#38;1 automatically. In addition, we constantly protect your WordPress websites, through technical measures such as firewalls and filters, even before the updates have [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-9-7/\">WordPress 4.9.7 Update Available</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://community.1and1.com\">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"Matthias Pfefferle\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2732:\"<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/news/2018/07/wordpress-4-9-7-security-and-maintenance-release/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WordPress 4.9.7</a> is now available for download for all earlier WordPress versions. It also includes bugfixes and security improvements. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/news/2018/07/wordpress-4-9-7-security-and-maintenance-release/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Learn more</a></p>\n<h2>How to update?</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>As always, <strong>Managed WordPress websites will be updated by 1&amp;1 automatically.</strong><br />\n<span id=\"result_box\" class=\"\" lang=\"en\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"\">In addition, we <span id=\"result_box\" class=\"short_text\" lang=\"en\" tabindex=\"-1\">constantly</span> protect your WordPress websites, through technical measures such as firewalls and filters, even before the updates have been implemented.</span></span></li>\n<li>If you have installed WordPress yourself or use a standard installation from the 1&amp;1 App Center, you can update to 4.9.7 from your WordPress <strong>Dashboard. </strong>From there, select <strong>Updates</strong> and click <strong>Update Now</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you prefer to update manually, you can <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/download/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">download WordPress 4.9.7 here</a>.</p>\n<h2>Learn more about WordPress 4.9</h2>\n<p>WordPress 4.9 brings important improvements and new functions for the Customizer so that you can more easily adjust your site’s design. You can now send a link to share drafts of your changes with your team, publish changes at scheduled times and even lock your changes from editing by other designers.</p>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-9944\" src=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/wordpress-4-9-img-5.png\" alt=\"wordpress-4-9-img-5\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/wordpress-4-9-img-5.png 2560w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/wordpress-4-9-img-5-300x141.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/wordpress-4-9-img-5-768x360.png 768w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/wordpress-4-9-img-5-1024x480.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" />\n<p>WordPress 4.9 also offers a new gallery widget and an improved text widget that supports images, audio and videos.</p>\n<p><a class=\"promo-button\" href=\"https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-9/\">Learn more about WordPress 4.9</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-9-7/\">WordPress 4.9.7 Update Available</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://community.1and1.com\">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:49:\"https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-9-7/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"4\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"Use Local Google Fonts (Web Fonts) for WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"https://community.1and1.com/use-local-google-fonts-web-fonts-wordpress/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"https://community.1and1.com/use-local-google-fonts-web-fonts-wordpress/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 28 May 2018 06:41:29 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"How-To\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"WCMS\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Web Hosting\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Advanced\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Beginner\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"https://community.1and1.com/?p=10097\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:609:\"<p>The new General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) took effect starting on 05/25/2018. This will result in a lot of changes for you as a website operator. This also applies to the Google web fonts that you use in your WordPress installation. This article does not constitute legal advice on the subject of data protection, nor does [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://community.1and1.com/use-local-google-fonts-web-fonts-wordpress/\">Use Local Google Fonts (Web Fonts) for WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://community.1and1.com\">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3:\"jab\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8722:\"<p>The new <a href=\"https://www.1and1.com/digitalguide/websites/digital-law/general-data-protection-regulation-new-rules-for-businesses/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">General Data Protection Regulation</a> (GDPR) took effect starting on 05/25/2018. This will result in a lot of changes for you as a website operator. This also applies to the Google web fonts that you use in your WordPress installation.</p>\n<p>This article does not constitute legal advice on the subject of data protection, nor does it claim to be complete. Rather, we want to show you how to integrate web fonts quickly and easily into your website without retrieving the Google fonts from the Google servers.</p>\n<p>Of course, there are several ways to reach your goal. We would like to introduce one of them to you.</p>\n<p>Many free and commercial WordPress themes use the Google Fonts as a feature for the typographic design of your WordPress website. For you as a user, the easy integration and quality of these fonts is a convenient thing. The problem with these fonts in connection with GDPR is the external availability via Google servers.</p>\n<hr />\n<h2>Google Fonts and Privacy Policy</h2>\n<p>Every time you visit your WordPress website, Google Fonts that are not integrated locally are loaded directly from the Google servers. The following data is transmitted to Google, among others:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Name and version of the browser</li>\n<li>Website (referrer) from which the Google Fonts were requested</li>\n<li>Operating system and screen resolution</li>\n<li>IP address of the user</li>\n<li>Language settings of the browser</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This personal data is transmitted to Google and processed at the latest when the IP address of the accessing user is transmitted. After May 25, 2018, you must notify your website visitors in your privacy statement that &#8211; and why &#8211; you submit personal data to Google in order to present the website with sent fonts.</p>\n<p>But you can prevent the transmission of data to Google with a simple trick by retrieving the used web fonts directly from your domain. This allows you to bypass the Google servers and may improve the loading times of your website.</p>\n<hr />\n<h2>Use local Google Fonts for WordPress: The preparations</h2>\n<p>With five simple steps you prepare your website for the use of local web fonts.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Select the desired font using <a href=\"https://google-webfonts-helper.herokuapp.com/fonts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">google-webfonts-helper</a>.</li>\n<li>Select the desired font styles by clicking on the boxes (multiple selection possible).</li>\n<li>Customize the path (e.g. <strong>/wp-content/fonts/</strong>).</li>\n<li>Copy the CSS snippet and save it in a text file named <strong>franklin.css</strong> on your hard drive.<a href=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/google-webfonts-helper_overview.png\"><img src=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/google-webfonts-helper_overview.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1522\" height=\"1101\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-10104\" srcset=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/google-webfonts-helper_overview.png 1522w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/google-webfonts-helper_overview-300x217.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/google-webfonts-helper_overview-768x556.png 768w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/google-webfonts-helper_overview-1024x741.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1522px) 100vw, 1522px\" /></a></li>\n<li>Download the required files and unzip the ZIP archive into a folder named <strong>fonts</strong> on your local PC.<a href=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/google-webfonts-locale.png\"><img src=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/google-webfonts-locale.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"986\" height=\"596\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-10106\" srcset=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/google-webfonts-locale.png 986w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/google-webfonts-locale-300x181.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/google-webfonts-locale-768x464.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 986px) 100vw, 986px\" /></a></li>\n</ol>\n<hr />\n<h2>Extend WordPress with Additional CSS Code for Google Fonts</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Load the folder &#8220;fonts&#8221; into the folder specified in the  <strong>google-webfonts-helper</strong> to your web space. In this example, this is the path <strong>/wp-content/fonts</strong>.</li>\n<li>Check in your WordPress theme where you can specify your <strong>own CSS settings</strong>.<br />\nFor this example, the following <strong>Additional CSS</strong> must be added directly in the <strong>Customizer</strong>.</p>\n<pre>/* libre-franklin-900 - latin */\r\n@font-face {\r\nfont-family: \'Libre Franklin\';\r\nfont-style: normal;\r\nfont-weight: 900;\r\nsrc: url(\'/wp-content/fonts/libre-franklin-v2-latin-900.eot\'); /* IE9 Compat Modes */\r\nsrc: local(\'Libre Franklin Black\'), local(\'LibreFranklin-Black\'),\r\nurl(\'/wp-content/fonts/libre-franklin-v2-latin-900.eot?#iefix\') format(\'embedded-opentype\'), /* IE6-IE8 */\r\nurl(\'/wp-content/fonts/libre-franklin-v2-latin-900.woff2\') format(\'woff2\'), /* Super Modern Browsers */\r\nurl(\'/wp-content/fonts/libre-franklin-v2-latin-900.woff\') format(\'woff\'), /* Modern Browsers */\r\nurl(\'/wp-content/fonts/libre-franklin-v2-latin-900.ttf\') format(\'truetype\'), /* Safari, Android, iOS */\r\nurl(\'/wp-content/fonts/libre-franklin-v2-latin-900.svg#LibreFranklin\') format(\'svg\'); /* Legacy iOS */\r\n}\r\n/* libre-franklin-900italic - latin */\r\n@font-face {\r\nfont-family: \'Libre Franklin\';\r\nfont-style: italic;\r\nfont-weight: 900;\r\nsrc: url(\'/wp-content/fonts/libre-franklin-v2-latin-900italic.eot\'); /* IE9 Compat Modes */\r\nsrc: local(\'Libre Franklin Black Italic\'), local(\'LibreFranklin-BlackItalic\'),\r\nurl(\'/wp-content/fonts/libre-franklin-v2-latin-900italic.eot?#iefix\') format(\'embedded-opentype\'), /* IE6-IE8 */\r\nurl(\'/wp-content/fonts/libre-franklin-v2-latin-900italic.woff2\') format(\'woff2\'), /* Super Modern Browsers */\r\nurl(\'/wp-content/fonts/libre-franklin-v2-latin-900italic.woff\') format(\'woff\'), /* Modern Browsers */\r\nurl(\'/wp-content/fonts/libre-franklin-v2-latin-900italic.ttf\') format(\'truetype\'), /* Safari, Android, iOS */\r\nurl(\'/wp-content/fonts/libre-franklin-v2-latin-900italic.svg#LibreFranklin\') format(\'svg\'); /* Legacy iOS */\r\n}</pre>\n</li>\n<li>Add the CSS snippet from your previously saved file franklin.css in the WordPress backend using <strong>franklin.css</strong> in the WordPress backend using <strong>Appearance</strong> &gt; <strong>Customize</strong> &gt; <strong>Additional CSS</strong>.<br />\n<a href=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/customize_additional_css.gif\"><img src=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/customize_additional_css.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"1440\" height=\"810\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-10110\" /></a><br />\nThe functionality <strong>Additional CSS </strong> is already included in the WordPress core. Therefore, every modern WordPress theme should support this function. If your WordPress theme does not allow additional CSS, then you can retrofit this function, for example, using the following plugin: <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-add-custom-css/\">WP Add Custom CSS</a> This alternative option also works with all our Managed WordPress installations.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>For example, to check your changes, you can use the Google Chrome browser <a href=\"https://developers.google.com/web/tools/chrome-devtools/?utm_source=dcc&amp;utm_medium=redirect&amp;utm_campaign=2018Q2\">DevTools</a>. There you will see that the font Libre Franklin is no longer loaded by Google, but by your domain.</p>\n<a href=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/wordpress-google-fonts-external_local.png\"><img src=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/wordpress-google-fonts-external_local.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"908\" height=\"869\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-10102\" srcset=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/wordpress-google-fonts-external_local.png 908w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/wordpress-google-fonts-external_local-300x287.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/wordpress-google-fonts-external_local-768x735.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 908px) 100vw, 908px\" /></a>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://community.1and1.com/use-local-google-fonts-web-fonts-wordpress/\">Use Local Google Fonts (Web Fonts) for WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://community.1and1.com\">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"https://community.1and1.com/use-local-google-fonts-web-fonts-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"3\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"WordPress 4.9.6 released, includes improvements for GDPR\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:44:\"https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-9-6/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-9-6/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 17 May 2018 06:00:17 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Information\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"https://community.1and1.com/?p=10087\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:604:\"<p>WordPress 4.9.6 is now available for download for all earlier WordPress versions. It introduces improvements that help you adjust your websites to be compliant to the new General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), that will come into force on 25 May 2018. It also includes bugfixes and security improvements as well as some minor user experience [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-9-6/\">WordPress 4.9.6 released, includes improvements for GDPR</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://community.1and1.com\">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Philipp Bellmann\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3021:\"<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/news/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WordPress 4.9.6</a> is now available for download for all earlier WordPress versions. It introduces improvements that help you adjust your websites to be compliant to the new <a href=\"https://www.1and1.com/digitalguide/websites/digital-law/general-data-protection-regulation-new-rules-for-businesses/?ac=OM.US.USo50K361081T7073a\">General Data Protection Regulation</a> (GDPR), that will come into force on 25 May 2018. It also includes bugfixes and security improvements as well as some minor user experience changes. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/news/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Learn more</a></p>\n<h2>How to update?</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>As always, <strong>Managed WordPress websites will be updated by 1&amp;1 automatically.</strong><br />\n<span id=\"result_box\" class=\"\" lang=\"en\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"\">In addition, we <span id=\"result_box\" class=\"short_text\" lang=\"en\" tabindex=\"-1\">constantly</span> protect your WordPress websites, through technical measures such as firewalls and filters, even before the updates have been implemented.</span></span></li>\n<li>If you have installed WordPress yourself or use a standard installation from the 1&amp;1 App Center, you can update to 4.9.6 from your WordPress <strong>Dashboard. </strong>From there, select <strong>Updates</strong> and click <strong>Update Now</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you prefer to update manually, you can <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/download/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">download WordPress 4.9.6 here</a>.</p>\n<h2>Learn more about WordPress 4.9</h2>\n<p>WordPress 4.9 brings important improvements and new functions for the Customizer so that you can more easily adjust your site’s design. You can now send a link to share drafts of your changes with your team, publish changes at scheduled times and even lock your changes from editing by other designers.</p>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-9944\" src=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/wordpress-4-9-img-5.png\" alt=\"wordpress-4-9-img-5\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/wordpress-4-9-img-5.png 2560w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/wordpress-4-9-img-5-300x141.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/wordpress-4-9-img-5-768x360.png 768w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/wordpress-4-9-img-5-1024x480.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" />\n<p>WordPress 4.9 also offers a new gallery widget and an improved text widget that supports images, audio and videos.</p>\n<p><a class=\"promo-button\" href=\"https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-9/\">Learn more about WordPress 4.9</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-9-6/\">WordPress 4.9.6 released, includes improvements for GDPR</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://community.1and1.com\">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:49:\"https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-9-6/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"Meet the new 1&amp;1 WordPress Assistant\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"https://community.1and1.com/new-1and1-wordpress-assistant/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"https://community.1and1.com/new-1and1-wordpress-assistant/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 19 Feb 2018 09:12:26 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Information\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"Products & Features\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"What\'s new\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"https://community.1and1.com/?p=10023\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:395:\"<p>With the new 1&#038;1 WordPress Assistant you can set up your site, pick a design you like and automatically install essential plugins in one step.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://community.1and1.com/new-1and1-wordpress-assistant/\">Meet the new 1&#038;1 WordPress Assistant</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://community.1and1.com\">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"Gaelle Despoulain\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3955:\"<p>With the new 1&amp;1 WordPress Assistant you can set up your site, pick a design you like and automatically install essential plugins in one step.</p>\n<p>Many of you might have noticed the changes we introduced since November 2017. We released a new version of the 1&amp;1 WordPress Assistant that was a lot friendlier while using the classic design approach.</p>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-9972\" src=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mwp-assistant-teaser-en_us.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" srcset=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mwp-assistant-teaser-en_us.png 2560w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mwp-assistant-teaser-en_us-300x169.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mwp-assistant-teaser-en_us-768x432.png 768w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mwp-assistant-teaser-en_us-1024x576.png 1024w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mwp-assistant-teaser-en_us-500x281.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" />\n<p>We took the existing three-step-process that included a complicated plugin-selection page and replaced it with a simpler one-step-solution to help you set up a use case and a design (theme), choosing the recommended plugins for you automatically.</p>\n<h2>So, what changed in the last releases?</h2>\n<p>But, of course, progress never stops and the plan wasn’t to end there. We wanted to help you focus on your goals using a distraction-free design.</p>\n<p>That&#8217;s why we rebuild the Assistant to have its own space, its own design, and an even clearer interface, by hiding unnecessary menus and elements.</p>\n<p><strong>Simplified design selection</strong>: While the functionalities of the Assistant stay roughly the same, with WordPress 4.9.3 we gave the use case &amp; theme setup a makeover:</p>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-10027\" src=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/assistant-use-case-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1786\" srcset=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/assistant-use-case-1.png 2560w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/assistant-use-case-1-300x209.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/assistant-use-case-1-768x536.png 768w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/assistant-use-case-1-1024x714.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" />\n<p><strong>New login screen</strong>: The WordPress login screen has a new, matching look as well, taking you from the installation step to an almost live-ready website in a very smooth, yet pretty and uncomplicated way. Simply use your e-mail adress or WordPress username to login to your website.</p>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-10029\" src=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/login-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1452\" srcset=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/login-1.png 2560w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/login-1-300x170.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/login-1-768x436.png 768w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/login-1-1024x581.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" />\n<h2>And what’s for the future?</h2>\n<p>A lot of improvements and cool stuff will be coming next, as we want to continuously improve your WordPress experience and help you get online as quick as possible.</p>\n<p>But the most important thing is: we want to work with you, for you! Your feedback is greatly appreciated and we will be glad to hear what you think in the comments section.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://community.1and1.com/new-1and1-wordpress-assistant/\">Meet the new 1&#038;1 WordPress Assistant</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://community.1and1.com\">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"https://community.1and1.com/new-1and1-wordpress-assistant/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2:\"18\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5